



Feb. 12. 1781.



The Executive will advance 20,000 to Messrs. Lewis and Thornton on the 12th. of March, and will agree to the terms proposed in Mr. Lewiss letter of Feb. 6. 1781. reserving a liberty to pay for the powder in tobacco @ 20/ the hundred or its worth in paper money as valued by the grand jury next preceding paiment.

Th: Jefferson

